 ## Structure
 
-> TBC
+Updatecli manifests follow a standard layout within each repository:
+
+```
+repo/
+├── updatecli/
+│   ├── bump.yml              # Main dependency bump manifest
+│   ├── values.d/
+│   │   └── scm.yml           # SCM configuration values
+│   └── policies/             # Local policies (if not using shared)
+└── .github/workflows/
+    └── updatecli.yml          # GitHub Actions workflow trigger
+```
+
+- **Manifests** (`updatecli/*.yml`) define what to update, using `sources`, `conditions`, and `targets`
+- **Values files** (`values.d/`) provide environment-specific configuration (e.g., SCM tokens, branch names)
+- **The workflow** triggers updatecli via `elastic/oblt-actions/updatecli/run@v1`
+
+For shared policies used across multiple repositories, see the [elastic/oblt-updatecli-policies](https://github.com/elastic/oblt-updatecli-policies) repository.
 
