 ## Local development
 
-> TBC
+To test updatecli manifests locally before pushing to CI:
+
+1. **Install updatecli:**
+
+   ```bash
+   brew install updatecli/updatecli/updatecli
+   ```
+
+2. **Run in diff mode** (dry run — shows what would change without applying):
+
+   ```bash
+   export GITHUB_TOKEN=$(gh auth token)
+   updatecli diff --config updatecli/bump.yml
+   ```
+
+3. **Apply changes locally** (creates PRs or commits):
+
+   ```bash
+   updatecli apply --config updatecli/bump.yml
+   ```
+
+4. **Test with values files:**
+
+   ```bash
+   updatecli diff --config updatecli/bump.yml --values updatecli/values.d/scm.yml
+   ```
+
+Refer to the [Updatecli quick start](https://www.updatecli.io/docs/prologue/quick-start/) for more details.
