+# macOS Runners for the CI/CD
 
-> TBC
+macOS runners are used for building and testing projects that require Apple hardware — primarily Beats and Agent on macOS/ARM.
+
+## Available Environments
+
+| Environment | Use Case | Documentation |
+|-------------|----------|---------------|
+| Orka (self-managed) | General macOS CI workloads | [Orka setup](orka.md) |
+| Orka for Beats | Beats-specific macOS builds | [Orka for Beats](orka-for-beats.md) |
+
+## When to Use macOS Runners
+
+- Building or testing macOS-specific binaries (`.pkg`, `.dmg`)
+- Running integration tests that require Apple hardware or macOS APIs
+- Validating ARM64 (Apple Silicon) compatibility
+
+## Getting Access
+
+macOS runner access is managed through the Observability CI team. See the [Orka setup guide](orka.md) for VPN and credential requirements.
