 #### Legacy: Service Account Keys (If Still in Use)
 
-**AWS:** `TBC`
+**AWS:**
+
+To rotate legacy AWS service account keys:
+1. Log in to the AWS Console for the affected account
+2. Navigate to IAM > Users > select the service account
+3. Create a new access key under Security credentials
+4. Update the key in Vault CI or the relevant secret store
+5. Verify dependent pipelines pass, then deactivate and delete the old key
+
+**Preferred alternative:** Migrate to OIDC/Keyless authentication to eliminate long-lived credentials entirely. See [Keyless documentation](./keyless/index.md).
+
+**GCP:**
+
+To rotate legacy GCP service account keys:
+1. Open the [GCP Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/iam-admin/serviceaccounts) for the project
+2. Select the service account, go to Keys tab
+3. Create a new JSON key and download it
+4. Update the key in Vault CI or the relevant secret store
+5. Verify dependent pipelines pass, then delete the old key from GCP
 
